===Etymology===
{{etystub}}<br>
Most terrier breeds were developed to hunt [[vermin]] both over and under the ground. The word terrier comes from the Middle French terrier and before that the Latin 'terra', meaning [[earth]].
===Noun===
'''terrier'''
# A small dog from a group of small, lively [[dog]] [[breed]]s.

